			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">or Pet Crit AA.
<br />

<br />
Today i enabled the crits displays on my comp to check damage (because i had read something about that some time ago) while agro kitting in PoFire, to see the improvement over non crit hits (not the frequency, just the damage increase from regular hits to crit hits)
<br />

<br />

<br />
I was using <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3310&amp;source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Saryrn's Companion</a> augmented with the <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=28144" target="_blank" class="postlink">Gloves of Dark Summoning</a>
<br />
It's max hit is 76, max BS is 228
<br />
I have Death Fury 5
<br />
Pet was buffed with <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3305&amp;source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Rune of Death</a> and <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3178&amp;source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Vallon's Quickening</a>
<br />
It therefore had +65 STR, +41 ATK, +33 DEX (no idea if it has an influence on pet crits, but may as well note it), no other buff
<br />

<br />
Crit values:
<br />
Maximum crit hit was 125, which is a 64.4% increase over base hit, maximum BS hit was 383 which is a 68 (67.98...)% increase over base hit...
<br />

<br />
% increase is clearly not consistant, not a fixed value for a fixed level of Death Fury: if it had been say 68% rounded down (leading to BS' 383), the crit regular hit would be 127, if it had been 64% rounded up BS would have been 374, if it had been 65% rounded down BS would have been 376
<br />

<br />
Which leads me to the strange conclusion that Death Fury effect varies with the pet's hit.
<br />
And tells me that i'll have to test Child of Bertox and LoZ and do some parses with weapons<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11243" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://masklinnscans.free.fr/pninja.jpg" border="0" /></a>
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>balidet RZ/AD wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">do you really feel the need to stack [...] dots on boss mobs?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Balidet, you win EQ</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
