				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">yes, that's about the same conclusion i arrived at with my 25 minute parse with Death's Fury 5.
<br />

<br />
I made a post about it on the old forum but it's gone now, along with my parses..
<br />

<br />
death's fury 5 gave an increase in total pet dps of about 3-4% though by my test.
<br />

<br />
The damage increase from a crit is not a fixed % over the base damage it would do as you noticed.. which leads me to believe that they either fucked it up somehow, or there is a formula that i don't know which they are using to determine what the damage from the crit hit is.
<br />

<br />
For the time being I used 2/3 as the multiplier for crit damage since that seems to be what it's closest to.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
